CRYSTALS-Dilithium Reference Implementation — License & Provenance
==================================================================

SPDX-License-Identifier: CC0-1.0 OR Apache-2.0 OR GPL-2.0-only

This directory vendors the reference implementation of CRYSTALS-Dilithium
(standardized by NIST as FIPS-204 ML-DSA), from the PQ-Crystals project:

    https://github.com/pq-crystals/dilithium

The public API symbols (pqcrystals_dilithium2_ref_*) and the source layout
(sign.c, poly.c, polyvec.c, ntt.c, packing.c, reduce.c, rounding.c, params.h,
symmetric-shake.c, api.h) are from that upstream.

----------------------------------------------------------------------
Upstream license — verbatim, from pq-crystals/dilithium/LICENSE:

    Public Domain (https://creativecommons.org/share-your-work/public-domain/cc0/);
    or Apache 2.0 License (https://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0.html) or GPL 2.0 License (http://www.gnu.org/licenses/gpl-2.0.html).

    For Keccak and the random number generator
    we are using public-domain code from sources
    and by authors listed in comments on top of
    the respective files.
----------------------------------------------------------------------

Accordingly, `fips202.c` / `fips202.h` (Keccak / SHAKE) and the randombytes
implementation are public-domain code by their respective authors; see the
comments at the top of those files for the upstream provenance.

Soqucoin modifications
----------------------
This copy carries Soqucoin-specific hardening — for example the
`soqucoin_memcleanse` secret-key zeroization added in `sign.c` for Halborn
audit finding FIND-028. Such modifications by The Soqucoin Core developers are
contributed under the project's MIT license (see the repository root `COPYING`)
and do not alter the upstream Public-Domain / Apache-2.0 / GPL-2.0 terms above
for the original PQ-Crystals code.
